<subSubSection id="C343BD964B12FF905C940C7FAC04FED2" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE6EE1D4B12FF905C940C7FAC04FED2" blockId="53.[151,1436,151,364]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="B92D320F4B12FF905C940C7FA857FE9F" bold="true" box="[198,319,263,289]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C59959E4B12FF905E3E0C70AB88FE9F" baseAuthorityName="Townsend" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[620,736,264,290]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dexia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavida">
<emphasis id="B92D320F4B12FF905E3E0C70ABE9FE9F" box="[620,641,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92D320F4B12FF905EDD0C70AB88FE9F" box="[655,736,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">flavida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from it in having broad gena which is more than 1/2 eye height, distinct black inner vittae on postsutural scutum, more broad pruinosity on abdominal tergites, and dense yellowish white pruinosity on anterior 1/2 of tergite 5. We have not seen a male of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
